<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; Responsible for creating and driving their sales pipeline.<br />
&bull; Capture leads and use closed-loop lead management to ensure assignment and follow-up by others.<br />
&bull; Maintain knowledge of competitors in account.<br />
&bull; Use specialty expertise to seek out new opportunities and expand and enhance existing opportunities to build the pipeline in and drive pursuit.<br />
&bull; Provide support to Account Managers and provide input regarding business development and solution expertise.<br />
&bull; Development of quota objectives and future direction for defined product category.<br />
&bull; Establish a professional, working, and consultative, relationship with the client, up to and including the C-level for mid-to-large accounts, by developing a core understanding of the unique business needs of the client within their industry.<br />
&bull; May invest time working with and leveraging external partners to deliver sale.<br />
&bull; Directs or coordinates supporting sales activities.</p>
<p>
<strong>Scope and Impact</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; Works on multiple size accounts.<br />
&bull; May perform project management role.<br />
&bull; May invest time working external partners.<br />
&bull; Significant percentage of time spent directly with customer; interfaces with all levels, including highest within customer organization.<br />
&bull; Develop business plan in conjunction with senior leadership.<br />
&bull; Typically assigned higher than average quota.</p>
<p>
<strong>Education and Experience Requirements</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; Native Spanish and excellent English communication skills.<br />
&bull; University or Bachelor&#39;s degree.<br />
&bull; Desired directly related previous work experience (software or hardware for electronic voting systems and the like).<br />
&bull; Demonstrated achievement of progressively higher quota, diversity of business customer, and higher level customer interface.<br />
&bull; Extensive selling experience within industry and on similar products.<br />
&bull; Typically 5-10 years of advanced sales experience.<br />
&bull; Project management skills required.<br />
&bull; 2-3 years of product sales in the desired specialty.</p>
<p>
<strong>Knowledge and Skills Requirements</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; Is considered an expert in knowledge of products, solution or service offerings as well as competitor&#39;s offerings to be able to sell integrated solutions.<br />
&bull; Understands the industry and market segment in which key accounts are situated, and integrates this knowledge into consultative selling.<br />
&bull; Understands and applies program/project management methods and processes to define, plan, cost, resource, track and ensure successful pursuit.<br />
&bull; Account planning and accurate account revenue forecasting skills.<br />
&bull; Collaborates with management and sales teams in shared accounts to ensure seamless integration of specialist sales with other sales activities.<br />
&bull; Cultivates &amp; maintains positive relationships with customers to ensure account retention &amp; growth, and position the company as the preferred vendor for meeting all business needs.<br />
&bull; Demonstrates leadership and initiative in successfully driving specialty sales in accounts - prospecting, negotiating and closing deals.<br />
&bull; Deep knowledge of products, solution or service offerings as well as competitor&#39;s offerings.<br />
&bull; Properly utilizes CRMs to accurately forecasts business.<br />
&bull; Understands and sells high value software solutions.<br />
&bull; Understands selling of services sales.<br />
&bull; Leverages services as part of strategic product sales.<br />
&bull; Maintain expertise of industry trends, associated solutions, and key partner solutions.</p>
<p>
<strong>Critical competencies to drive business results</strong></p>
<p>
<u>New Business Acquisition</u><br />
Aggressively searches for opportunities in new or existing accounts, expanding business market share.<br />
<br />
<u>Opportunity Qualification, Development and Closing</u><br />
Assesses feasibility of pursuing an opportunity given what the customer is trying to accomplish, competitive presence and strength, and risk of proceeding. Defines and positions well-targeted solutions to generate customer acceptance, develop internal company buy-in, and wins the deal.<br />
<br />
<u>Planning and Alignment</u><br />
Supports the development of account plans that focus sales activities, ensure accurate forecasts, and integrate specialist-selling seamlessly within an overall account strategy.<br />
<br />
<u>Customer Relationship Management</u><br />
Demonstrates customer-sensitive practices within accounts<br />
<br />
<u>Sales Effectiveness Fundamentals</u><br />
Tools &amp; Resources Utilization, Businesses &amp; Offers, Competitive Positioning, Organizational Collaboration.</p>
