			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Candidate Profile</strong></p>
<p>
This is a new role being created for a quota bearing salesperson and will focus on the sales of electoral modernization software solutions within the Indian sub-continental region (India, Sri Lanka, Bangladesh, Bhutan, Nepal, Maldives).</p>
<p>
The position will report directly to the Head of Sales AsiaPAC and there is scope for advancement with business growth. This is a predominantly self-autonomous and challenging role that requires the right candidate to show ownership, enthusiasm, professionalism and an entrepreneurial spirit towards business. This is a role where a reasonable amount of travel within the region will be required.</p>
<p>
The role would suit someone who is currently in a commercial role, selling software solutions/services into the Indian sub-continental market place. Significant knowledge of the sales cycle/process of procurement in central and local government within the region is highly advantageous to be successful in this position.</p>
<br />
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; Quota responsibility for the region.<br />
&bull; Plan, execute and report on region strategy and business plan.<br />
&bull; Identifying customers for Scytl solutions particularly in the public sector in the region.<br />
&bull; Managing the relationship with the key people of the partners of Scytl in the region<br />
&bull; Providing online or face-to-face demonstrations/presentations.<br />
&bull; Perform consultative selling with potential customers.<br />
&bull; Attending customer sites and regional events to promote the products/services<br />
&bull; Gathering of market knowledge and working with key stakeholders to enhance products/services further.<br />
&bull; Receipt and processing of customer orders.<br />
&bull; Account management of customer accounts.<br />
&bull; Regular reporting of sales pipeline and current opportunities.<br />
&bull; Securing and closing deals with our partners and customers.</p>
<p>
<strong>Experience Requirements</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; Written At least 5 years of experience in commercial, sales or business development positions in companies providing technological solutions or software in the Indian region.<br />
&bull; Experience in selling complex IT solutions in the public sector, with a good knowledge of both local and national government procurement procedures in the region.<br />
&bull; Proven quota bearing experience.<br />
&bull; Experience in achieving new accounts or in opening new markets.<br />
&bull; Experience in consultative sales.<br />
&bull; Solid knowledge of software concepts.<br />
&bull; Experience managing sales teams will be a plus.</p>
<p>
<strong>Personal abilities required</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; The seniority and drive for long cycles of sales transactions.<br />
&bull; Results driven and entrepreneurial.<br />
&bull; A strategic approach, understanding of business principles.<br />
&bull; Keen negotiation skills.<br />
&bull; Sales driven and sales motivator.<br />
&bull; A self-motivated individual, not afraid of challenge.<br />
&bull; Ability to work under pressure.<br />
&bull; Energetic and enthusiastic, with inherent drive and determination.<br />
&bull; High level of social skills, with the ability to influence at all levels.<br />
&bull; Good communication and interpersonal skills.</p>
<p>
<strong>Job Advantages</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; International working environment.<br />
&bull; Creative and results focused team.<br />
&bull; Opportunity to be part of the worldwide leader in its market.</p>
<p>
<strong>Compensation &amp; Benefits</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; Competitive salary + commissions.</p>
