			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Company introduction</strong></p>
<p>
Scytl is an international technology company providing state-of-the-art electronic voting and electoral modernization solutions. Scytl covers the entire scope of election modernization, from advising Governments to implementing solutions to assist them in their productivity, transparency and accessibility efforts.</p>
<p>
Being internationally recognized for its expertise, Scytl has managed around 100,000 electoral events electronically in more than 20 countries throughout the world over the last 10 years including the USA, Mexico, France, Norway, Switzerland, Austria, BiH and India.</p>
<p>
Its groundbreaking electoral security technology is protected by international patents and enables to carry out electronically all types of electoral processes in a completely secure and auditable manner, positioning the company as a worldwide leader in the industry.</p>
<p>
<strong>Candidate Profile</strong></p>
<p>
The Project Manager is the person that takes ownership of the projects and coordinates the activities and the assigned resources to provide the agreed deliverables with the expected quality and in a timely manner.</p>
<p>
To successfully perform this task, the candidate must have previous proven experience managing projects and negotiating both scope and deadlines with clients, (preferably in public as well as private organizations) as well as reporting in to General Management or C level.</p>
<p>
We are looking for someone with a background in IT projects (preferably those that include complex customized software developments), who possesses a solid technical background and a great deal of experience in Project Management methodologies.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; Take ownership of project planning and delivery.<br />
&bull; Liaise and negotiates with internal departments and external clients to ensure adequate development and delivery.<br />
&bull; Coordinate the activities of partners and providers where necessary.<br />
&bull; Manage project changes and new requests, and incorporate them into the plan.<br />
&bull; Collaborate in the analysis and functional definition of technical project requirements.<br />
&bull; Report both horizontally and vertically in a timely basis.<br />
&bull; Anticipate issues and sort them out.<br />
&bull; Collaborate in writing papers for international conferences.</p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; University degree in Computer Science, Telecommunications or equivalent.<br />
&bull; Project Management certification (PMI or PRINCE2) or equivalent knowledge is paramount.<br />
&bull; Knowledge in software development lifecycle and requirements gathering.<br />
&bull; Excellent knowledge of English both spoken and written. Other languages will be a plus.<br />
&bull; Good communication skills.<br />
&bull; Good team worker with leadership skills.<br />
&bull; Availability to travel worldwide sometimes on a short notice.<br />
&bull; International experience will be a plus.<br />
&bull; Knowledge of Agile software development methodologies will be a plus.<br />
&bull; Knowledge on the following technologies: web based applications, cryptography and digital security will be a plus.</p>
<p>
<strong>Job Advantages</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; International working environment.<br />
&bull; Creative and results focused team.<br />
&bull; Opportunity to be part of the worldwide leader in its market.<br />
&bull; Being part of a full-fledged Project Management Office.<br />
&bull; Great office in Barcelona center.<br />
<br />
<strong>Compensation &amp; Benefits</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; Competitive compensation.<br />
&bull; Benefits such as private medical insurance, restaurant tickets, etc.</p>
]]></description>
