			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Company introduction</strong></p>
<p>
Scytl is an international technology company providing state-of-the-art electronic voting and electoral modernization solutions. Scytl covers the entire scope of election modernization, from advising Governments to implementing solutions to assist them in their productivity, transparency and accessibility efforts.</p>
<p>
Being internationally recognized for its expertise, Scytl has managed around 100,000 electoral events electronically in more than 20 countries throughout the world over the last 10 years including the USA, Mexico, France, Norway, Switzerland, Austria, BiH and India.</p>
<p>
Its groundbreaking electoral security technology is protected by international patents and enables to carry out electronically all types of electoral processes in a completely secure and auditable manner, positioning the company as a worldwide leader in the industry.</p>
<p>
<strong>Candidate Profile</strong></p>
<p>
Within the Sales Operations team, the Pre-sales Consultant is in charge of managing the completion and handover of project and tender proposals for our clients and prospects. This is a key position with a great deal of involvement in the sales process and a decisive influence in the achievement of each deal.<br />
In order to be able to perform this task, the pre-sales consultant needs to possess a solid technical background and proven experience in pre-sales, consulting or project management endeavors, always facing the client and having to put together complex IT proposals or projects.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; Plan and manage complex tender answers and unsolicited proposals.<br />
&bull; Assess requirements and craft appropriate solutions that are sound and cost-effective.<br />
&bull; Produce cost and effort estimations when assessing tenders and opportunities.<br />
&bull; Provide direct support to the sales department in technical presentations to customers and partners.<br />
&bull; Create presentations and other support material for the sales department.<br />
&bull; Study and divulge internally certification processes and regulations about e-voting.<br />
&bull; Collaborate in the writing of user and deployment manuals and guides.<br />
&bull; Collaborate in writing papers for international conferences.</p>
<br />
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; University degree in computer science, telecommunications or equivalent level.<br />
&bull; Previous relevant experience in an IT environment.<br />
&bull; Native or equivalent knowledge of English both spoken and written. Other languages will be a plus.<br />
&bull; Great communicator, creative and analytical. Able to present complex technicalities in an easy to understand manner.<br />
&bull; Proven experience in working together with sales people for the technical part of highly customized sales proposals.<br />
&bull; Advanced user of the MS Office package, especially Power Point, Project, Word and Excel.<br />
&bull; Results driven. Able to prioritize effectively when dealing with multiple proposals and deadlines.<br />
&bull; Ability for teamwork.<br />
&bull; Availability to travel worldwide, sometimes on short notice.<br />
&bull; Knowledge on the following technologies: web based applications, cryptography (PKI, digital signature...) and digital security will be a plus.<br />
&bull; Experience in public sector contracting will be a plus.<br />
&bull; Experience in international tendering processes will be a plus.<br />
&bull; Knowledge of software development lifecycles and requirements gathering will be a plus.</p>
<p>
<strong>Job Advantages</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; International working environment.<br />
&bull; Creative and results focused team.<br />
&bull; Opportunity to be part of the worldwide leader in its market.<br />
&bull; Great office in Barcelona centre.<br />
<br />
<strong>Compensation &amp; Benefits</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; Competitive salary + performance bonus.<br />
&bull; Benefits such as private medical insurance, restaurant tickets, etc.</p>
