			<title><![CDATA[Software Engineering Technical Manager]]></title>
			<department><![CDATA[Software Engineering]]></department>
			<team><![CDATA[Software Engineering]]></team>
			<url><![CDATA[http://scytl.theresumator.com/apply/1X3xXc/Software-Engineering-Technical-Manager.html]]></url>
			<city><![CDATA[Barcelona]]></city>
			<state><![CDATA[]]></state>
			<country><![CDATA[Spain]]></country>
			<postalcode><![CDATA[08006]]></postalcode>
			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Candidate Profile</strong></p>
<p>
The Technical Manager leads mission critical development teams that are responsible for delivering the projects to our clients. Liaising with the Project Manager in charge of any given project, the Technical Manager collaborates in estimating the resources needed, assembling the dynamic teams for any given project, acting as the technical lead for that project and coordinate all necessary activities. Delivery on time is paramount, so the Technical Manager needs to leverage resources and assess and act on any situation wth the objective of compliance with the delivery plan.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; Manage a team of 5 to 15 Software Engineers, QA Engineers, Functional Analysts and Systems Engineers.<br />
&bull; Provide the software development effort estimates to the Project Manager.<br />
&bull; Identify and escalate technical risks to the Project Manager.<br />
&bull; Validate requirements provided by Functional Analysts.<br />
&bull; Assigns tasks to the members of the Technical Team.<br />
&bull; Control the technical decisions in a project.<br />
&bull; Perform hands-on activities when needed.<br />
&bull; Occasionally travel to participate in software deployment.</p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; English advanced user, both spoken and written.<br />
