			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Company Introduction</strong></p>
<p>
Scytl is the global leader in secure election management and electronic voting solutions. Specializing in election modernization technologies, Scytl offers the first end-to-end election management and voting platform, providing the highest security and transparency standards currently available.</p>
<p>
Scytl has capitalized on its more than 18 years of research to develop election-specific cryptographic security technology protected by more than 40 international patents and patent applications, positioning Scytl as the company with the largest patent portfolio of the industry.</p>
<p>
Scytl&rsquo;s solutions have been successfully used in more than 20 countries throughout the world over the last 10 years, including Canada, the United States, Mexico, Ecuador, France, Norway, Switzerland, Bosnia-Herzegovina, the UAE, India and Australia. Scytl is headquartered in Barcelona, Spain with strategic offices in Canada, the United States, Peru and Greece as well as field offices in the UK, Ukraine, Malaysia, India and Brazil.</p>
<p>
<strong>Candidate Profile</strong></p>
<p>
We are looking for an experienced Quality Assurance Engineer who will integrate within the development team and will be in charge of making sure that we deliver strong and reliable solutions to our clients in the field of Electoral Modernization.</p>
<p>
The position is based in the company&rsquo;s Development Centre in Athens.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; Develop and execute comprehensive test plans, design test methods, test cases and other documentation for functional and regression testing<br />
&bull; Perform varied tests such as requirements, functional, configuration, security and regression testing<br />
&bull; Document test execution.<br />
&bull; Enter bugs and report status with accurate details, and follow up on them.<br />
&bull; Identify potential automation areas; design and build automated tests, Interpret and analyze test results.<br />
&bull; Document traceability between testing and system requirements documentation.<br />
&bull; Complete assigned tasks on-time and in accordance with the appropriate process.<br />
&bull; Regular status reports of testing activities to the QA Director</p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; Written and spoken English at Negotiation level.<br />
&bull; University degree in computer science, or equivalent level<br />
&bull; At least 2 years in a similar position<br />
&bull; Good knowledge of formal testing techniques<br />
&bull; Experience working with open source tools, libraries and products<br />
&bull; Basic knowledge of a programming language such as Java</p>
<p>
The following would be an advantage:<br />
&bull; Knowledge of cryptography: PKI, PKCS<br />
&bull; Knowledge of Java (J2SE, J2EE)<br />
&bull; Experience with Automation Recording tools ( Selenium, Windmill,&nbsp; Watir, FitNess )<br />
&bull; Knowledge of data access applications development (SQL, JDBC). Oracle DB is preferred, though knowledge on other databases is welcome.</p>
<p>
<strong>Job Advantages</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; International working environment.<br />
&bull; Creative and results focused team.<br />
&bull; Opportunity to be part of the worldwide leader in its market.<br />
&bull; Opportunity to collaborate with a large distributed development team.</p>
